org.apache.taverna.server.master.defaults

Interface Default


  • public interface Default
    This defines a collection of default values, collecting them from various parts of the server.
    Author:
    Donal Fellows

    • Field Summary

      Fields 
      Modifier and Type Field and Description
      static String AUTHORITY_PREFIX
      The default value of the prefix property.
      static String[] CERTIFICATE_FIELD_NAMES
      What fields of a certificate we look at when understanding who it is talking about, in the order that we look.
      static String CERTIFICATE_TYPE
      The type of certificates that are processed if we don't say otherwise.
      static int CREDENTIAL_FILE_SIZE_LIMIT
      Max size of credential file, in kiB.
      static String[] EXTRA_ARGUMENTS
      The extra arguments to pass to the subprocess.
      static String NOTIFY_MESSAGE_FORMAT
      The notification message format to use if none is configured.
      static String PASSWORD_FILE
      Default value for LocalWorkerState.passwordFile.
      static String REGISTRY_JAR
      The name of the resource that is the implementation of the subprocess that acts as the RMI registry.
      static String RMI_PREFIX
      Prefix to use for RMI names.
      static int RUN_COUNT_MAX
      Maximum number of runs to exist at once.
      static int RUN_LIFE_MINUTES
      Initial lifetime of runs, in minutes.
      static int RUN_OPERATING_LIMIT
      Maximum number of Status.Operating runs at any time.
      static String SECURE_FORK_IMPLEMENTATION_JAR
      The name of the resource that is the implementation of the subprocess that manages secure forking.
      static String SERVER_WORKER_IMPLEMENTATION_JAR
      The name of the resource that is the implementation of the subprocess that this class will fork off.
      static String SMS_GATEWAY_URL
      The address of the SMS gateway service used.
      static int SUBPROCESS_START_POLL_SLEEP
      Polling interval to use during startup, in milliseconds.
      static int SUBPROCESS_START_WAIT
      How long to wait for subprocess startup, in seconds.
